Chapter: Gravitational Field Intensity for Different Bodies > Section: 8.4 - Intensity due to a Point Mass

Suppose a point mass $M$ is placed at point $O$, then gravitational field intensity due to this point mass at point $P$ is given by

$$

\begin{array}{c}

M \\

\stackrel{\text{O}}{\longleftarrow} r \stackrel{\text{F}}{\longrightarrow} \bullet P \\

I = \frac{GM}{r^2}

\end{array}

$$

